  "analysis": "The vsnprintf doesn't handle the `.` precision specifier in format strings like `%.3d`. When it encounters `.`, it doesn't know what to do and skips the width, outputting `%.3` literally. Need to fix vsnprintf to handle precision.",
  "plan": "Fix vsnprintf in my_stdlib.c to handle precision specifier, rebuild and test.",
